do any thing. Do not be angry with me, dearforgive
me, and do with me what thou wilt;yet do not tell me
so plainly that thou art dyingO, nonor of what thou
couldst dono, no don't do that;do any thing but that.
That
will kill me. Nothing else can. My parents, my
poor parentsthey know that I am not made like other
women;nay, why remind thee of that. Unnatural as
I was to them, thou implacable man, what have I been to
